        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 4:54PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles south of Sheridan, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Banner.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
